<br>
The impact of Poisons v3, if it comes about, will depend on which of several different scenarios of accessibility to the ingredients and the costs involved per dose actually materialise.<br>
<br>
<b>1. Easily accessed ingredients, low cost</b>: Rogues would probably be expected to use poisons virtually all the time; at raids, in XP groups, anywhere. Rogues without good poisoning abilities may well end up at a disadvantage. If you could carry multiple doses of a finished poison in one slot ("stackable" for this discussion) then rogues will find it greatly advantageous to carry a range of effects with them. Soloing will become easier (or possible for some) and may even be economic.<br>
<br>
